# Folder Structure

Follow this layout. Do not create new top-level folders without a clear reason.

## `src/` — application source

- `src/App.tsx` — root component. Keep it thin; move logic into child components early.
- `src/main.tsx` — entry point. Do not put app logic here.
- `src/index.css` — the **one and only** stylesheet in the project (see the styling rule).
- `src/components/ui/` — shadcn/ui primitives only. Generated by the shadcn CLI. Do not hand-edit these files except to add documented variants.
- `src/components/` (outside `ui/`) — application components composed from shadcn primitives. One component per file; file name in PascalCase matches the exported component.
- `src/lib/` — pure helpers (formatters, parsers, small utilities). Starts with `utils.ts` (shadcn's `cn` helper). Functions here should not use React.
- `src/hooks/` — custom hooks. Folder exists; add files here when extracting reusable stateful logic **after the second duplication**, not before.
- `src/pages/` — route-level components. **Create this folder only when a router is introduced**, and ask the user before introducing one.
- `src/types/` — shared type definitions. **Create this folder only when a type is genuinely shared across 2+ files**. Until then, define types next to where they are used.

## `public/` — static assets

Everything placed here is served at the root URL (no `public/` prefix in the URL).

- `public/data/` — data files (CSV, JSON, …).
- `public/logos/` — logo assets.
- `public/images/` — image assets.
- `public/favicon.svg` — site favicon.

If the user adds a file to `public/data/foo.csv`, it is fetched from the app as `fetch("/data/foo.csv")` — **not** `fetch("/public/data/foo.csv")`.

## Repo root — configuration only

- `index.html` — Vite entry HTML.
- `package.json`, `package-lock.json` — npm.
- `tsconfig.json`, `tsconfig.app.json`, `tsconfig.node.json` — TypeScript.
- `vite.config.ts` — Vite configuration (includes the `@/*` path alias and the Tailwind plugin).
- `eslint.config.js` — ESLint flat config.
- `components.json` — shadcn/ui configuration.
- `README.md` — participant-facing onboarding.

## `docs/` — workshop material

Contains briefing cards and the presenter guide. **Treat these as read-only**. Do not modify them unless the user explicitly asks.

## Import paths

- Imports from anywhere in `src/` use the `@/` alias (e.g. `import { Button } from "@/components/ui/button"`).
- Sibling files in the same folder may use relative imports (`./foo`).
- Never use long `../../../` chains.
